>It's a device you spin on your drill that has small 'stones' on it that
>are used to slightly grind the inside of a cylinder.  Your local auto
>parts store should have them.

See
http://www.sears.com/data/product_images/tools/large/00904656000-dlv.jpg
for a picture.  It is the same idea as a hone you might use on your
engine cylinders, but smaller.  

